## IX. LATE MEDIEVAL/EARLY MODERN TENSIONS

### Scholasticism vs. Humanism
- Abstract philosophy vs. practical wisdom
- Latin technical terms vs. eloquent rhetoric
- Monastic withdrawal vs. civic engagement
- Reconciled by some (Erasmus), divided by others

### Faith vs. Reason
- Aquinas: Harmony
- Ockham: Separate spheres
- Scotus: Will over intellect
- Reformation: Scripture over reason
- Renaissance: Reason renewed importance

### Church vs. State
- Medieval: Church supreme (Papal plenitudo potestatis)
- Conciliarism: Church councils above Pope
- Reformation: National churches
- Machiavelli: State autonomous from Church

### Individual vs. Community
- Medieval: Community/Church primary
- Renaissance: Individual dignity, achievement
- Reformation: Individual conscience, faith
- But: All still embedded in community

